						               													<description>Crossroads, Closing the Gap&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A World War 2 Mini-Campaign detailing the actions of the 4th Canadian Armoured Brigade at the Battle of Saint-Lambert-sur-Dives.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A 49 page Campaign Book, featuring background, force lists and 7 missions in accurately mapped locations.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;CAMPAIGN STRUCTURE: A 2 part linked campaign showing the initial Canadian advance into St Lambert, following up with the German counter-attack and push to break out of the Falaise Gap through the town. Complete with multiple victory conditions, including a method to track the teetering morale of the German forces at the time.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;MISSIONS: Detailed mission maps based off a master campaign map, taken from 1944 1:25,000 General Staff maps. These maps provide the mission battlegrounds for the campaign.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;'FORCE LISTS: Entries for Canadian Infantry, German Infantry and Fallschirmjager troops. Historical support lists are also provided for each force.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;BACKGROUND: A look into the 4th Canadian Armoured Brigade and the German defenders of St Lambert.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;SUPPORTED SYSTEMS: Created for the Chain of Command wargame, this campaign module is also compatible with Bolt Action, Flames of War and I Ain't Been Shot Mum.&amp;#10;Being a campaign module, the information present should be useable by most wargames with some modification.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
